# Commits and Releases

Commitlint enforces Conventional Commits. semantic-release bumps version on merge to `main`.

| Commit type | Version bump |
|-------------|--------------|
| `feat:` | minor |
| `fix:`, `perf:` | patch |
| `feat!:` or `BREAKING CHANGE:` | major |
| `docs:`, `style:`, `refactor:`, `test:`, `build:`, `ci:`, `chore:` | none |

```bash
git commit -m "feat: add user authentication"
git commit -m "fix: resolve mobile menu not closing"
```

Use `feat!:` or `BREAKING CHANGE:` in the body for breaking changes.
